Some words by @lorenzmira_lapland :- " Some nights are easy but this was definitely one of the most difficult Aurora hunt of the season.. I went through all the way to Swedish Lapland 2hour drive to get out of the clouds but it was not enough Northern lights are faint and barely visible so I waited.. graphs were looking good but the bz field was highly positive .. waited and the same time start driving towards the south beacuse there were clouds coming From the #North ...

At 2.30am the bz dropped -10 negative and I knew at that point that was north to wait and I convinced everybody to be patient that we would have seen something worth the last night !!

The only problem was the sunrise that would start to lighta up the sky around 3.40 in the night but at 3.30am we started to see something and it devloped in an amazing pink and blue arc that explode over our head giving us a beautiful aurora DanceğŸ˜»

I arrived back at home 7.00am but everyone was happy âœŒï¸
